Note.Content: It appears that the actual words that Cain spoke have been omitted.
MT-K וְאָמַר לו | MT-Q וְאָמַר לֹא

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = action by which humans and deities utter words; this can happen within their minds and be inaudible to others, but in most cases the words are spoken out loud in order to communicate something to others; usually directly followed by the actual words that are spoken
= action by which humans refer to a particular object when speaking
= action by which humans give verbal instructions regarding something
= action by which humans and deities make a very solemn statement concerning something
= action by which humans utter words about themselves, usually with the purpose of drawing all attention to themselves
